  + [role] is deterministic_numeric_and_symbolic_processing
  + [not_role] is theorem prover, RH proof assistant, inference agent, hidden reasoning engine, or zero certification authority

  = must: use explicit precision for high-precision arithmetic
  = must: produce inspectable JSON or CSV output for reusable numerical traces
  = must: include proof_status metadata stating that outputs are finite numerical traces, not proof or certification
  = must: keep scripts runnable from the project root with the project .venv
  = must: include tests for representative small computations
  = must: keep numerical results separate from interpretation, classification, and dense-node inference
  = must: fail loudly on invalid ranges, nonpositive steps, and unsupported output formats
  - never: claim proof, disproof, zero certification, or theorem-level authority from tool output
  - never: import old ReasoningFramework symbolic modules as runtime authority

## Tool Set

& [ZetaEvaluationTool] is the script surface for direct zeta value processing
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\zeta_eval.py
  + [input] is sigma, t, precision, and output_format
  + [output] is zeta value real, imaginary, absolute value, argument, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is numerical_trace_not_proof

& [CriticalLineScanTool] is the script surface for sampling Hardy Z and zeta on the critical line
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\critical_line_scan.py
  + [input] is t_min, t_max, step, precision, and optional zero refinement
  + [output] is sample rows, sign-change brackets, optional numerical zero estimates, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is sign_change_probe_not_zero_certification

& [ZeroProbeTool] is the script surface for known nontrivial zero lookup and residual processing
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\zero_probe.py
  + [input] is start_index, count, and precision
  + [output] is mpmath zero ordinates, zeta residuals, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is library_numeric_lookup_not_independent_certification

& [FunctionalEquationCheckTool] is the script surface for finite residual checks of zeta and xi functional equations
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\functional_equation_check.py
  + [input] is sigma, t, precision, and equation
  + [output] is left side, right side, residual, relative residual, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is finite_residual_check_not_proof

& [PrimeCountCompareTool] is the script surface for prime-count baselines
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\prime_count_compare.py
  + [input] is integer sample points and optional Riemann R truncation terms
  + [output] is pi(x), logarithmic integral estimate, Riemann R estimate, and errors
  + [proof_status] is finite_arithmetic_comparison_not_asymptotic_proof

& [SpecialPrimeProfileTool] is the script surface for special-prime family profiling
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\special_prime_profile.py
  + [input] is explicit integer primes or the default Fermat-prime and 641 seed set
  + [output] is Fermat-prime identity, Fermat-number divisor hits, Mersenne, Proth, Pierpont, safe, Sophie Germain, and base-2 Wieferich facts
  + [proof_status] is finite_prime_family_profile_not_rh_evidence

& [SpecialPrimeScanTool] is the script surface for bounded special-prime family scanning
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\special_prime_scan.py
  + [input] is finite prime bound and maximum Fermat-number divisor index
  + [output] is bounded family member lists for selected special-prime classes
  + [proof_status] is bounded_prime_family_scan_not_rh_evidence

& [PrimeFamilyDistributionTool] is the script surface for returning special-prime family probes to whole-field distribution objects
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\prime_family_distribution.py
  + [input] is finite sample points or generated bounds, selected families, and precision metadata
  + [output] is pi(x), li(x), R(x), theta(x), psi(x), family counts, family densities, and family theta shares
  + [proof_status] is finite_family_distribution_probe_not_rh_evidence

& [PrimeFamilyIntervalDistributionTool] is the script surface for interval-level whole-field return
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\prime_family_intervals.py
  + [input] is finite interval endpoints and selected families
  + [output] is interval prime-count, theta, psi, family-count, and family-theta increments
  + [proof_status] is finite_family_interval_probe_not_rh_evidence

& [PrimePowerDecompositionTool] is the script surface for decomposing psi into prime-power layers
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\prime_power_decomposition.py
  + [input] is finite sample points or interval endpoints and optional event inclusion
  + [output] is theta layer, higher-prime-power layers, psi totals, interval movement, and optional prime-power events
  + [proof_status] is finite_prime_power_decomposition_not_rh_evidence

& [ExplicitFormulaProbeTool] is the script surface for bounded explicit-formula error probes
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\explicit_formula_probe.py
  + [input] is finite sample points, zero pair counts, precision metadata, and optional zero-term inclusion
  + [output] is pi(x), theta(x), psi(x), explicit-formula estimates, zero-pair sums, constant/trivial corrections, and residual rows
  + [proof_status] is finite_explicit_formula_probe_not_zero_certification

& [ZeroWindowProbeTool] is the script surface for bounded sharp and smoothed zero-term window probes
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\zero_window_probe.py
  + [input] is finite sample points, zero pair counts, window modes, precision metadata, and optional zero-term inclusion
  + [output] is pi(x), theta(x), psi(x), windowed explicit-formula estimates, weighted zero-pair sums, residuals, and optional weighted zero-term rows
  + [proof_status] is finite_zero_window_probe_not_zero_certification

& [EulerProductProbeTool] is the script surface for finite Euler-product and logarithmic-derivative weighting probes
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\euler_product_probe.py
  + [input] is finite s samples with sigma > 1, prime bounds, precision metadata, and optional term inclusion
  + [output] is zeta(s), finite Euler products, -zeta'(s)/zeta(s), prime-factor logarithmic-derivative sums, prime-power cutoff sums, and residual rows
  + [proof_status] is finite_euler_product_log_derivative_probe_not_rh_evidence

& [SigmaBoundaryProbeTool] is the script surface for Euler-product approach-to-boundary probes
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\sigma_boundary_probe.py
  + [input] is finite sigma values greater than 1, t values, prime bounds, and precision metadata
  + [output] is zeta/log-derivative residual rows with distance_to_sigma_1 and adjacent-sigma transition ratios
  + [proof_status] is finite_sigma_boundary_probe_not_critical_line_evidence

& [TAxisBoundaryProbeTool] is the script surface for fixed-sigma t-axis Euler-product probes
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\t_axis_boundary_probe.py
  + [input] is finite sigma values greater than 1, nonnegative t values, prime bounds, and precision metadata
  + [output] is zeta/log-derivative residual rows with t-axis annotations and adjacent-t transition ratios
  + [proof_status] is finite_t_axis_boundary_probe_not_zero_line_evidence

& [VerticalResonanceScanTool] is the script surface for dense fixed-sigma vertical resonance scans
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\vertical_resonance_scan.py
  + [input] is finite sigma values greater than 1, t range, step, prime bounds, precision metadata, and max sample guard
  + [output] is regular vertical sample rows and finite local-extrema candidate rows for selected metrics
  + [proof_status] is finite_vertical_resonance_scan_not_zero_line_evidence

& [ExponentialShiftProbeTool] is the script surface for bounded modular probes of base^exponent + shift forms
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\exponential_shift_probe.py
  + [input] is base, exponent list, shift list, small factor limit, and max hit count
  + [output] is parity, forced divisibility rules, bounded small prime divisors, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is bounded_exponential_shift_probe_not_primality_proof

& [ExponentialPowerShiftProbeTool] is the script surface for bounded modular probes of base^(exponent_base^power) + shift forms
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\exponential_power_shift_probe.py
  + [input] is base, exponent base, exponent power list, shift list, small factor limit, and max hit count
  + [output] is parity, forced divisibility rules, bounded small prime divisors, and metadata
  + [proof_status] is bounded_power_exponent_shift_probe_not_primality_proof

& [CoefficientPowerShiftProbeTool] is the script surface for bounded modular probes of coefficient * power_base^N + shift(N) forms
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\coefficient_power_shift_probe.py
  + [input] is coefficient, power base, powers, fixed shifts, shift modes, small factor limit, and max hit count
  + [output] is bounded small prime divisors and metadata for each shifted coefficient-power row
  + [proof_status] is bounded_coefficient_power_shift_probe_not_primality_proof

& [IrregularPrimeScanTool] is the script surface for bounded irregular-prime scans
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\irregular_prime_scan.py
  + [input] is finite prime bound and optional regular-prime inclusion
  + [output] is irregular primes, irregular indices, Bernoulli indices, and zeta special-value annotations
  + [proof_status] is finite_irregular_prime_scan_not_zero_line_evidence

& [IrregularPrimeDistributionTool] is the script surface for returning irregular-prime probes to whole-field distribution objects
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\irregular_prime_distribution.py
  + [input] is finite sample points or generated bounds, precision metadata, and optional member inclusion
  + [output] is pi(x), theta(x), psi(x), irregular-prime counts, irregular-prime density among odd primes, and irregular theta share
  + [proof_status] is finite_irregular_prime_distribution_not_zero_line_evidence

